               <p>First London Jury - Before Mr. Sergeant Arabin.</p>
               <p>272. 
               <persName id="t18261207-269-defend1467" type="defendantName">
                  EDWARD 
                  ROBINSON
               <interp inst="t18261207-269-defend1467" type="surname" value="ROBINSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261207-269-defend1467" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261207-269-defend1467" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261207-269-defend1467" type="age" value="21"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for <rs id="t18261207-269-off1557" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18261207-269-off1557" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261207-269-off1557" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18261207-269-cd1558" type="crimeDate">7th of December</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261207-269-off1557 t18261207-269-cd1558"></join>, 1 handkerchief, value 6d., the goods of 
                     <persName id="t18261207-269-victim1468" type="victimName">
                        Charles 
                        Cunningham
                     <interp inst="t18261207-269-victim1468" type="surname" value="Cunningham"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18261207-269-victim1468" type="given" value="Charles"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18261207-269-victim1468" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261207-269-off1557 t18261207-269-victim1468"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>CHARLES CUNNINGHAM. I am a <rs id="t18261207-269-viclabel1559" type="occupation">mercer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261207-269-victim1468 t18261207-269-viclabel1559"></join>, and live in Bernard-street, Russell-square. On the 7th of December, I was in <placeName id="t18261207-269-crimeloc1560">Lothbury</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18261207-269-crimeloc1560" type="placeName" value="Lothbury"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18261207-269-crimeloc1560" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261207-269-off1557 t18261207-269-crimeloc1560"></join>, about five o'clock in the evening, and had a handkerchief in my coat pocket; I felt some one turn up my pocket; I turned round and saw the prisoner very near me: he passed me as I put my hand at my pocket: I examined my hat to see if it was there: - I then went and said to the prisoner, "Have you by chance found my handkerchief?" I saw it in his hand - he said Yes. I said I know where you found it, and detained him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18261207-269-person1469">
                  SAMUEL 
                  TURNER
               <interp inst="t18261207-269-person1469" type="surname" value="TURNER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261207-269-person1469" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261207-269-person1469" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I took him in charge, with the handkerchief - he said he had picked it up, but it was a rainy dirty evening, and the handkerchief was quite clean.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I saw it laying in a door-way - a gentleman saw me pick it up, but I have not had time to send for him.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18261207-269-verdict1561" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18261207-269-verdict1561" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 21.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18261207-269-punish1562" type="punishmentDescription">
